projects.name: EZCommit
projects.description: A set of tools for logs parsing and CI enhancement. It includes a Jenkins plugin to parse build logs, which has a prominent Web UI log viewer with features like styling, filtering, folding, search, lazy loading and so on. Another big part of the project is Web UIs for internal Cisco build-boosting tools. There are also a couple of smaller parts like web log viewer (a separate application), PEG parser (open sourced), CLI tool for parsing, and some others.

projects.name: STCez
projects.description:
Web application for building, running, and getting reports for Spirent TestCenter (STC) test cases of various
    methodologies. MethodologyCenter is aimed to provide simplified UI to cover advanced use cases of STC users. 
    
    The application allows to answer network answers faster, without requiring expert knowledge of the underlying test tool. 
    Spirent TestCenter is a number one L2-3 network testing hardware (and software in a form of VM) around the world.

projects.name: TRex
projects.description:
Network packet editor. This is a JavaFX application, which is able to create network packets from scratch or import/edit existing PCAP files. Packet editor uses Scapy library to build and edit network packet. Scapy server is located at the remote TRex instance and communicates with desktop application via ZMQ our responsibility is a JavaFX application(TRex packet editor), Scapy server and integration with trex-stateless-gui(existing GUI for TRex load generator) 
    https://trex-tgn.cisco.com/trex/doc/index.html

projects.name: Aastha
projects.description:
Aastha Enterprise is a network testing tool, which generates L4-L7 network traffic(initially HTTP). Consists of agent instances(agent application, which spawns a dummy server and a load generator, which acts as a client) located on real hardware or in a VM, and the management web application, which can connect to remote nodes, define test scenarios, configure nodes/network interfaces, run tests and show statistics/charts. 
This project is currently on prototyping stage, information will be updated. Further stages should add support for more protocols and TCP stack customizations

projects.name: NBI/API
projects.description:
Prime APIs - a set of HTTP APIs to access data and invoke operations of Prime Infrastructure. Used by customers willing to integrate PI as well as by PI engineering internally. 
    Built on top of XMP NBI framework, which is a part of XMP platform (which is what PI is built on). XMP NBI provides means to enable HTTP access to the XMP database, a common structure for defining operations and restricted role-based access.

projects.name: STAR
projects.description:
The objective of the STAR project is to measure the impact of the Developer Experience Improvement initiative. These improvements can be measured in various dimensions, but a key aspect is the productivity improvements that should result from the different programs.
    In order to measure productivity improvements, we must first agree on measurement systems, then apply those systems at various points in the lifespan of the Developer Experience Initiative. If we have chosen the appropriate measurement system, we should be able to see tangible proof of these  improvements.

projects.name: Telemetry
projects.description:
Cisco Telemetry collector is a PI component, which automatically collects anonymous data about PI product and transmits it to Cisco. Is used to help Cisco improving their products constantly. Collected data includes version, system information, performance metrics, networks information etc. 
    Another part of Telemetry(pi-metrics) is responsible for a processing of collected data, creating charts, tables, reports, and managing customer's feedback. 
    info: PI -> Administration / Settings / System Settings / Help Us Improve

projects.name: Velocity
projects.description:
Velocity allows to: 
    Manage device infrastructure in a friendly fashion
    Provide exclusive access to resources in the inventory
    Draw network topologies in Web graphical editor
    Automatically configure and test topologies
    Deploy virtual topologies into IaaS clouds
    Get reports about resource utilization
    Schedule test case execution and get reports 

    Velocity Platform features: 
    Polyglot RESTful service architecture in the backend (Java/EJB, Python/Django right now, more are coming)
    UI middleware based on async IO technology (TBD)
    Single-page UI (ReactJS)
